h1. Enhanced Azure VM Terraform Module – Demo Documentation

h2. 1. Overview
This Terraform module provisions secure, enterprise-grade Azure Virtual Machines with advanced capabilities:

Disk encryption

Monitoring and diagnostics

Backup and disaster recovery

Snapshot-based recovery

Network security

Identity management

Policy compliance

High availability

VM lifecycle management

Supported OS: Windows and Linux
Integrations: Azure Monitor, Log Analytics, Recovery Services Vault, Azure Policy

h2. 2. Step-by-Step Architecture Flow

h3. Step 1 – Common Configuration
Resource: module "common"

Functionality:

Imports shared global configuration

Applies standard tags

Ensures consistent naming

Benefits:

Standardized infrastructure

Cost tracking through tags

Naming alignment across environments

h3. Step 2 – Network Discovery
Resources:

azurerm_virtual_network

azurerm_subnet

Functionality:

Fetches existing Virtual Network and Subnet for VM deployment

Benefits:

Network reuse

Integration with enterprise network

Security boundary compliance

h3. Step 3 – Network Interface
Resource: azurerm_network_interface

Features:

Accelerated networking

Static or dynamic private IP

IP forwarding support

Benefits:

High network performance

Flexible networking configuration

h3. Step 4 – Network Security Group
Resources:

azurerm_network_security_group

azurerm_network_security_rule

azurerm_network_interface_security_group_association

Features:

Dynamic rule creation

Support for existing NSG

Priority-based rules

Benefits:

Controlled network access

Secure inbound traffic

h3. Step 5 – User Assigned Identity
Resources:

azurerm_user_assigned_identity

data.azurerm_user_assigned_identity

Functionality:

Creates or references a Managed Identity

Benefits:

Secure authentication

No credentials stored

Key Vault access enabled

h3. Step 6 – Disk Encryption Setup
Resources:

azurerm_key_vault_key

azurerm_disk_encryption_set

azurerm_role_assignment

Features:

Key Vault integration

Automatic key rotation

Managed Identity authentication

Benefits:

Data protection

Compliance with security policies

h3. Step 7 – Data Disk Provisioning
Resources:

azurerm_managed_disk

azurerm_virtual_machine_data_disk_attachment

Disk Creation Options:

|| Option || Description ||
| Empty | New empty disk |
| Copy | Copy from existing disk |
| Restore | Restore from snapshot |
| FromImage | Create from VM image |
| Upload | Upload disk data |

Advanced Features:

On-demand bursting

Performance tier selection

Network access control

Trusted launch compatibility

Benefits:

Flexible disk management

Optimized performance

h3. Step 8 – Virtual Machine Deployment
Modules:

module.windows_vm

module.linux_vm

Features:

VM size configuration

OS disk management

Managed identities

Custom images

Boot diagnostics

h3. Step 9 – Trusted Launch Security

Features:

Secure Boot

Virtual TPM

Secure VM disk encryption

Benefits:

Protection against rootkits

Firmware-level security

h3. Step 10 – Monitoring Integration
Resources:

Azure Monitor Agent

Data Collection Rule

Diagnostic Settings

Capabilities:

Windows:

Performance metrics

Event logs

Dependency tracking

Linux:

Syslog collection

VM metrics

Performance monitoring

Benefits:

Full observability

Centralized logging

h3. Step 11 – Backup with Recovery Services Vault
Resource: module.recovery_services_vault

Backup Features:

Daily backups

90-day retention

Diagnostic integration

Important Fix:

Old: vm_id = local.calculated_vm_name

Fixed: vm_id = local.virtual_machine_id

Benefit:

Targets actual VM resource for backup

h3. Step 12 – Disk Snapshots
Resources:

azurerm_snapshot.os_disk

azurerm_snapshot.data_disk

Features:

Incremental snapshots

Snapshot tagging

Snapshot for every data disk

Benefits:

Fast recovery

Backup redundancy

h3. Step 13 – Azure Site Recovery
Resources:

Windows: azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.asr_windows

Linux: azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.asr_linux

Benefit:

Disaster recovery replication

Cross-region failover

h3. Step 14 – Azure Policy Compliance
Resources:

Windows: azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.guest_config_windows

Linux: azurerm_virtual_machine_extension.guest_config_linux

Benefit:

Security compliance

Governance enforcement

h3. Step 15 – Private Disk Access
Resource: azurerm_disk_access

Benefit:

Prevents public exposure of managed disks

Improves security posture

h3. Step 16 – VM Availability Monitoring
Resource: azurerm_monitor_metric_alert

Alert Trigger:

{code}
VM availability < 1
{code}

Benefit:

Immediate notification of VM outages

h3. Step 17 – Automatic Password Generation
Resource: random_password

Functionality:

Generates password if none provided

Benefit:

Secure credentials

Eliminates weak passwords

h2. 18. Key Enhancements in This Module

|| Category || Feature Highlights ||
| Security | Disk encryption, Trusted Launch, Guest configuration compliance, Private disk access |
| Backup & Recovery | Recovery Services Vault, OS & Data disk snapshots, Azure Site Recovery |
| Monitoring | Azure Monitor Agent, Log Analytics, Dependency Agent, Diagnostic settings, Availability alerts |
| Disk Management | Multiple disk creation methods, Performance tiers, On-demand bursting, Disk network access policies |
| Flexibility | Support for existing NSG, Placement options (Availability Set, Dedicated Host, Proximity Placement) |
| Lifecycle | Termination notifications, Hibernation support, Automatic patching, OS image notifications |

